21:25.718 --> 21:27.586 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
dead.

21:27.686 --> 21:31.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as thousands more face the
loss of their
homes or workplace, videographer
Bruno Federico

21:31.657 --> 21:37.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and special correspondent Nadja
Drost bring
us this report from Manabi
province on Ecuador's

21:37.229 --> 21:41.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
coast, where people are trying
to rebuild
their towns and lives.

21:41.800 --> 21:49.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALFREDO JAMA, Fisherman (through
translator):
That night was unforgettable. I
was bringing

21:49.675 --> 21:53.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
up the net, when, suddenly, I
felt the boat
vibrating too much. It was like
the floor

21:54.013 --> 21:55.781 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
burst open.

21:55.881 --> 22:01.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: It's the first time
that fisherman
Alfredo Jama has dared to return
out to sea

22:01.620 --> 22:06.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
since an earthquake caught him
by surprise
on April 16th when he was
fishing.

22:06.659 --> 22:11.764 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ALFREDO JAMA (through
translator): When I
looked around, I saw an
explosion that left

22:11.864 --> 22:16.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us without light. Everything was
dark. The
sea bellowed from beneath. It
was like there

22:16.101 --> 22:21.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was a beast coming up from
under. When I returned
to the house, everything was a
disaster.

22:22.041 --> 22:28.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Jama's wife, Paola
Farias, walked
us through what used to be the
two-story home

22:28.814 --> 22:32.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of their extended family, which
she also used
for her nail salon.

22:32.318 --> 22:37.122 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAOLA FARIAS, Salon Owner
(through translator):
When I said, don't worry, it's
over, was when

22:37.223 --> 22:43.662 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the movement started more
strongly. The walls
started falling. We managed to
leave the house.

22:43.762 --> 22:48.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was terrible, because imagine
how one works
so hard for one's things, and
from one moment

22:48.634 --> 22:50.469 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to another, nothing.

22:50.569 --> 22:57.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Farias is one of at
least 250,000
Ecuadorians directly affected by
an earthquake

22:57.142 --> 23:02.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that knocked down thousands of
buildings.
It also set off an outpouring of
support from

23:02.414 --> 23:07.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fellow Ecuadorians, like Karla
Morales, the
director of local human rights
group Kahre.

23:07.586 --> 23:13.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was at home in the city of
Guayaquil,
over 150 miles south of the
epicenter, the

23:13.425 --> 23:14.727 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
night the quake hit.

23:14.827 --> 23:18.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KARLA MORALES, Kahre: And in
that moment,
I just sent a tweet.

23:18.697 --> 23:23.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: "Bring supplies to
my house tomorrow,"
Karla wrote, and she'd drive
them north to

23:23.569 --> 23:26.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the earthquake-affected region
the next afternoon.

23:26.338 --> 23:31.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KARLA MORALES: And I didn't
expect that people
were so interested in helping
and with so

23:31.977 --> 23:40.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
much compassion and solidarity.
There were
like 600 or maybe 1,000 people
in my house,

23:40.386 --> 23:45.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bringing help and helping with
all that donations
that we were receiving in that
moment.

23:45.224 --> 23:50.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Karla ended up
sending 23 large
truckloads of materials that
day. Since then,

23:50.829 --> 23:55.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her team continues to distribute
donations,
from water filters to
mattresses, to rural

23:56.001 --> 24:00.339 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
areas, where help has been
slower to reach.

24:00.439 --> 24:08.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ecuador hadn't expected an
earthquake, but
preparing for a different
emergency, a volcanic

24:08.781 --> 24:13.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
eruption and flooding, helped it
respond quickly,
says Tim Callaghan of USAID.

24:13.752 --> 24:18.424 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIM CALLAGHAN, USAID: Many of
the countries
in this region, Peru, and
Paraguay, and including

24:18.524 --> 24:24.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ecuador, obviously were planning
for potential
negative impacts from El Nino
flooding. Thankfully,

24:24.196 --> 24:29.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that hasn't been as severe as
was forecast,
but it did force Ecuador and
other countries

24:29.501 --> 24:31.470 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to plan for emergencies.

24:31.570 --> 24:36.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: And that meant
Ecuador's government
already had a certain level of
resilience

24:36.975 --> 24:43.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and emergency coordination to
activate search-and-rescue
and channel aid to people, he
told us.

24:43.415 --> 24:48.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After getting frozen out of
Ecuador two years
ago for political reasons, USAID
is one of

24:48.454 --> 24:53.692 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
many international groups
sending experts
in. The U.S. has donated nearly
$3 million

24:53.792 --> 24:59.631 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of humanitarian aid towards
relief efforts.
The needs are still great.
Callaghan points

24:59.732 --> 25:05.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to water, sanitation and shelter
as the most
pressing.

25:05.437 --> 25:10.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Over 28,000 people are living in
shelters,
most run by the military. Others
are living

25:10.576 --> 25:16.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in parks or makeshift refuges,
where aid is
harder to come by. Its scarcity
led to this

25:16.315 --> 25:22.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
near brawl in Manta after people
outside the
neighborhood tried to claim
rations.

25:22.821 --> 25:31.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But as it looks towards renewal,
Ecuador first
has to ask some tough questions
over why the

25:31.764 --> 25:38.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
destruction was so extensive. As
municipal
employees in the city of
Portoviejo fly drones

25:38.103 --> 25:42.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to evaluate the damages, they
reveal a devastating
picture of what went wrong.

25:42.908 --> 25:47.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's a lot, says Patricio
Velez, the
head of territorial development
for the city

25:47.646 --> 25:49.415 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Portoviejo.

25:49.515 --> 25:53.485 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PATRICIO VELEZ, Head of
Territorial Development,
Portoviejo (through translator):
There was

25:53.585 --> 25:58.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a lot of informality,
constructions without
permits. People would add on a
third floor.

25:58.323 --> 26:03.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It took us by surprise. There
were new buildings
that collapsed and old ones that
stood up.

26:03.395 --> 26:08.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Ecuador is used to
plenty of
small quakes, and its building
code has developed

26:08.167 --> 26:13.305 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
over the years to include
seismic considerations,
says Jaime Argudo, a structural
engineer.

26:13.405 --> 26:18.777 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But he says that up to 85
percent of buildings
are constructed without planning
for an earthquake.

26:18.877 --> 26:24.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JAIME ARGUDO, Structural
Engineer: There is
also a major issue in our
country, and many

26:24.883 --> 26:29.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries around the world, that
building
codes are not properly enforced.

26:29.221 --> 26:35.227 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NADJA DROST: Now the
consequences of poor
building materials and
construction are devastatingly

26:35.327 --> 26:37.896 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
obvious.

26:37.996 --> 26:43.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Portoviejo, a city of 300,000
people, the
area hit hardest by the
earthquake was also

26:43.168 --> 26:49.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the city's economic center and
downtown. Here,
in what's being called the
city's ground zero,

26:49.174 --> 26:53.979 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
everything is shut down.
Two-thirds of buildings
inspected so far are either
collapsed, or

26:54.079 --> 26:59.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
severely damaged, and demolition
is in full
swing. Now, this battered city
faces rebuilding

26:59.952 --> 27:02.988 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
its economy, and its future.

27:03.088 --> 27:09.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As Velez points to how much of
ground zero
will be leveled, he also sees a
clean slate,

27:09.294 --> 27:13.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an opportunity for Portoviejo to
reinvent
itself and become more
resilient.

27:13.765 --> 27:19.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PATRICIO VELEZ (through
translator): The city
grew in a disorderly fashion,
without planning.

27:19.238 --> 27:21.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We should take advantage of this
moment now.

27:21.640 --> 27:26.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: But to carry out
new urban plans
and reconstruction across the
region will

27:26.778 --> 27:32.918 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
take big money, just as
Ecuador's economy
struggles against plummeting oil
prices.

27:33.018 --> 27:38.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Rafael Correa, an
economist, estimated
it could cost $3 billion. As he
surveyed the

27:38.857 --> 27:43.662 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
damages of a neighborhood
outside of Manta,
we asked how he plans to make
that happen.

27:43.762 --> 27:48.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAFAEL CORREA, President of
Ecuador (through
translator): We have a
contingency loan from

27:48.267 --> 27:54.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the World Bank and the IDB for
over $600 million.
We will probably reach over a
billion, and

27:54.573 --> 27:58.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we have taken a line of credit
that will give
us another billion dollars. If
all the lines

27:58.944 --> 28:04.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of credit work out, we will have
over $2 billion
for reconstruction. However, I
think we're

28:04.116 --> 28:07.452 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going to need more, but for the
short term,
it's a significant amount.

28:07.553 --> 28:11.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: The government has
taken several
special measures, such as
raising the national

28:11.456 --> 28:16.662 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
sales tax and getting
higher-income earners
to forego part of their salary,
to build up

28:16.762 --> 28:19.264 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
earthquake recovery funds.

28:19.364 --> 28:23.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some communities have already
had to rebuild
following a natural disaster.
Here in the

28:23.835 --> 28:30.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
town of San Vicente, Farias and
Jama's house
was first destroyed by an
earthquake in 1998.

28:30.842 --> 28:34.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After they rebuilt it, floods
from El Nino
washed it away.

28:34.212 --> 28:40.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAOLA FARIAS (through
translator): And now,
it fell, including the roof.
Three disasters

28:40.652 --> 28:46.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have happened to us, and thank
God we're alive,
and we have to keep going and
start rebuilding.

28:46.224 --> 28:51.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: But recovery will
take more than
reconstruction. reviving local
economies and

28:52.030 --> 28:57.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
people's livelihoods is a
pressing challenge,
yet slow to realize. But in
trying to figure

28:57.669 --> 29:01.506 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
out how, many residents are
thinking bigger,
says Morales.

29:01.607 --> 29:08.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KARLA MORALES: I think this has
been an earthquake
that destroyed houses, but
rebuilt minds.

29:08.680 --> 29:14.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the suffering, they are very
hopeful. They
are like, teach me. I want to
learn something

29:14.219 --> 29:15.921 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
else.

29:16.021 --> 29:19.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: While many look for
new ways
to make a living, others want to
restart their

29:19.825 --> 29:22.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
business. For Farias, that was
her nail salon.

29:22.361 --> 29:27.065 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAOLA FARIAS (through
translator): When the
house fell, you had to survive,
one way or

29:27.165 --> 29:32.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
another. When I saw there was
something left
of my business, I decided, OK, I
will start

29:32.270 --> 29:34.606 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
from zero. And here we are.

29:34.706 --> 29:41.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Farias and her
family want to
move to a new lot. It appears
they already

29:41.446 --> 29:43.815 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
know how to rebuild.

29:43.915 --> 29:48.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From Manabi province in Ecuador,
reporting
with Bruno Federico, I'm Nadja
Drost for the

29:48.620 --> 29:50.689 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"PBS NewsHour."

29:50.789 --> 29:56.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On our Web site,
learn about
a special mapping project that's
helping in

29:57.095 --> 30:02.934 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Ecuador's relief effort.

30:03.035 --> 30:12.911 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Stay with us.

30:13.011 --> 30:17.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
Making Sense
of patent trolls. Are they
protecting or stifling

30:17.816 --> 30:24.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
innovation? The launch of a
